✅ 1. Prerequisites (one-time)

In your GitHub repo:

Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret

Add:

DOCKER_USERNAME → devopslab1218
DOCKER_PASSWORD → (Docker Hub Access Token, not password)
✅ 2. Workflow file

Create:

.github/workflows/build-push.yml

✅ 4. Required project files

Your repo must contain:

project/
│── app.py
│── requirements.txt
│── Dockerfile   ✅
│── .github/workflows/build-push.yml

✅ 5. Dockerfile (required)
FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app

COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt

COPY . .

EXPOSE 5000

CMD ["python", "app.py"]
✅ 6. requirements.txt
flask
🚀 7. What happens

When you push:

git add .
git commit -m "add CI pipeline"
git push

👉 GitHub Actions will:

Checkout code
Set up Buildx
Build Docker image
Push to Docker Hub
✅ Expected Output
GitHub → Actions tab → Green check ✅
Docker Hub:
devopslab1218/python-app:latest
